                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/6183.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-02-16T19:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 16, 1913—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President of Mexico has sent telegrams to the governors of all the Mexican
                    States announcing military intervention. Mr. Lascurain, from whom I received
                    this information, characterizes this course as “very dangerous.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
